The paper deals with the representation and manipulation of simplicial complexes, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses algorithms for constructing Flag complexes and relaxed Delaunay complexes, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper proposes a new data structure for topological data analysis, which is a topic in scientific computing (cs.SI).
